summary:
The Release of Information Office received a package from the USPS which contained medical documents that were found loose in the mail or damaged by
mechanical processing equipment. The original package that was sent form Release of Information via certified mail contained approximately 600 pages, the
package that was returned from the USPS contained 200 pages. The ROI staff contacted USPS and reported that 400 pages were missing. The USPS entered a
claim and provided a claim number to ROI. At this point 400 pages are unaccounted for.
